GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 141
Short Title: The Joe John Remembrance Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Clampitt, White, Wheatley, and Reives (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Finance, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
February 18, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ENACT THE JOE JOHN REMEMBRANCE ACT TO REMOVE THE
3 ADDITIONAL FEE FOR A FIRE DEPARTMENT OR RESCUE SQUAD MEMBER
4 SPECIAL REGISTRATION PLATE.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. This act shall be known as the "Joe John Remembrance Act."
7 SECTION 2. G.S. 20-79.7 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 20-79.7. Fees for special registration plates and distribution of the fees.
9 …
10 (a1) Fees. – All other special registration plates are subject to the regular motor vehicle
11 registration fee in G.S. 20-87 or G.S. 20-88 plus an additional fee in the following amount:
12
13 Special Plate Additional Fee Amount
14 …
15 Ex-Prisoner of War None
16 Fire Department or Rescue Squad Member None
17 Gold Star Lapel Button None
18 …."
19 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025, and applies to special
20 registration plates issued or renewed on or after that date.
*H141-v-1*

